# Runtimes

Before running the cross-runtime example matrix, read
[`.cursor/example-runtimes.md`](../example-runtimes.md)
(runtimes, prerequisites, example contract, matrix commands, debugging).

The canonical runtime list is
[`tools/example_runtimes.toml`](../../tools/example_runtimes.toml) — read it
before running the matrix. Runtimes span MicroPython, CircuitPython, CPython
(incl. repo-root `.venv/bin/python` = `cpython-venv`), PyScript, and Jupyter.

**Platform** is the product category (see
[Portability & platforms](../../docs/platforms/index.md)); **runtime** is the
concrete executable or launcher used in automation.
